thread.title: Ole Miss' Nkemdiche suffers concussion

author: Jim Varney, USA TODAY Sports
title: Ole Miss' Nkemdiche suffers concussion
text:
Ole Miss' Nkemdiche suffers concussion USA Today Sports 6 hrs ago by Jim Varney, USA TODAY Sports Â© Justin Ford, USA TODAY Sports Justin Ford, USA TODAY Sports Robert Nkemdiche, the Ole Miss junior defensive lineman some project as the top pick in the 2016 NFL draft, suffered a concussion in the first quarter against Memphis and is out for the game.
Nkemdiche actually got hurt on offense, as the Rebels were using him to carry the ball in a short yardage situation.
AdChoices Nkemdiche has five solo tackles for a loss this season and with his brother, senior Denzel Nkemdiche, are regarded as the anchors of No. 12 Ole Miss' defense. Ole Miss led undefeated and 22nd-ranked Memphis 14-10 in the second quarter.
